{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892360684,"sessionID":"ses_284915426ffebAopU0o9o5uo4G","part":{"id":"prt_d7b6eedae001AaPIm7S0p4B9C5","messageID":"msg_d7b6ecbd7001LSeojddo3O3hZL","sessionID":"ses_284915426ffebAopU0o9o5uo4G","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-df8debf9d5f94751960d141523544893","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/integrations/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/integrations/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Integrations Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Normative requirements for the AgentCube Dify plugin integration and the PCAP analyzer example that uses AgentCube code interpreters and Kubernetes sandboxes.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: Dify plugin bootstrap and runtime\n10: \n11: The system SHALL expose a Dify-compatible Python plugin whose process entry runs the framework runner with a configured maximum request timeout.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: Plugin process starts\n14: \n15: - **GIVEN** the plugin package is installed with compatible `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk` versions\n16: - **WHEN** the platform starts the plugin using the manifest-declared entrypoint\n17: - **THEN** the plugin SHALL execute `main` which runs `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` until the host stops it\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ### Requirement: Plugin manifest structure\n22: \n23: The system SHALL ship a root `manifest.yaml` declaring plugin metadata, tool provider registration, resource permissions, and runner metadata sufficient for Dify to load and execute the plugin.\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Required manifest fields\n26: \n27: - **GIVEN** a valid plugin package root\n28: - **WHEN** the manifest is parsed by a Dify-compatible toolchain\n29: - **THEN** the manifest SHALL include `version`, `type: plugin`, `author`, `name`, `label` (multilingual map), `description` (multilingual), `icon`, `icon_dark`, `resource` (including `memory` and `permission` subtree), `plugins.tools` listing provider descriptors, and `meta` containing `version`, `arch`, `runner` (`language`, `version`, `entrypoint`), and `minimum_dify_version`\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Tool provider wiring\n32: \n33: - **GIVEN** the manifest `plugins.tools` references the Agentcube provider descriptor\n34: - **WHEN** the plugin is loaded\n35: - **THEN** Dify SHALL resolve `provider/agentcube.yaml` and associate it with the Python module declared under `extra.python.source`\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ### Requirement: Provider descriptor structure\n40: \n41: The system SHALL define a tool provider YAML that identifies the provider, lists its tools, and points to the Python provider implementation.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Provider lists tools and entry module\n44: \n45: - **GIVEN** `provider/agentcube.yaml` is present\n46: - **WHEN** the integration runtime resolves the provider\n47: - **THEN** the descriptor SHALL include `identity` (author, name, multilingual label/description, icon), a `tools` list including `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`, and `extra.python.source: provider/agentcube.py`\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ### Requirement: Tool parameter schema\n52: \n53: The system SHALL declare a tool schema for the code interpreter integration including connection endpoints, optional language selection, and code/command/session fields.\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Declared parameters match remote APIs\n56: \n57: - **GIVEN** `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`\n58: - **WHEN** an operator configures the tool in Dify\n59: - **THEN** the schema SHALL require string parameters `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`, SHALL offer optional `language` as a select among `python`, `javascript`, and `typescript`, and SHALL allow optional `code`, `command`, `session_id`, `session_reuse` (boolean), and `code_interpreter_id`, each documented for human and LLM-oriented forms\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ### Requirement: Tool provider credential validation\n64: \n65: The system SHALL implement credential validation on the tool provider class and SHALL surface validation failures using the Dify tool provider error type.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Invalid credentials are rejected\n68: \n69: - **GIVEN** an instance of `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider`\n70: - **WHEN** `_validate_credentials` encounters an error condition the implementer treats as invalid\n71: - **THEN** the provider SHALL raise `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` with a string message derived from the failure\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: Successful validation completes quietly\n74: \n75: - **GIVEN** credentials that satisfy the provider’s validation rules\n76: - **WHEN** `_validate_credentials` runs\n77: - **THEN** the method SHALL return without raising\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ### Requirement: Tool invocation and JSON messaging\n82: \n83: The system SHALL implement the Agentcube code interpreter tool as a Dify `Tool` that delegates execution and returns structured JSON to the host.\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: Dify invokes the tool\n86: \n87: - **GIVEN** a configured tool invocation with parameters matching the schema\n88: - **WHEN** Dify calls `_invoke` on `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool`\n89: - **THEN** the tool SHALL call `execute(**tool_parameters)` and SHALL yield `create_json_message(result)` for the outcome\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ### Requirement: Tool execution API surface\n94: \n95: The system SHALL implement `execute` with parameters for router and workload manager URLs, optional language, session controls, and code or command execution, delegating to `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient`.\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Code or command runs against configured endpoints\n98: \n99: - **GIVEN** valid `router_url`, `workload_manager_url`, and optional `language` defaulting to `python`\n100: - **WHEN** the tool receives `code` and/or `command` with optional `session_id`, `session_reuse`, and `code_interpreter_id`\n101: - **THEN** the tool SHALL use the AgentCube Python SDK client to perform the corresponding remote operations and SHALL return a JSON-serializable result object suitable for `create_json_message`\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ### Requirement: Plugin Python dependencies\n106: \n107: The system SHALL pin compatible versions of `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk` for reproducible installs.\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: Dependency bounds\n110: \n111: - **GIVEN** `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`\n112: - **WHEN** dependencies are installed in a clean environment\n113: - **THEN** installs SHALL satisfy `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n114: \n115: ---\n116: \n117: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer FastAPI service\n118: \n119: The system SHALL provide a FastAPI application that validates OpenAI-compatible configuration at startup, composes LangChain/LangGraph agents, and exposes an analysis endpoint for PCAP uploads.\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Startup requires API key\n122: \n123: - **GIVEN** the process is started without a usable `OPENAI_API_KEY` (or equivalent configured API key)\n124: - **WHEN** the application completes startup hooks\n125: - **THEN** startup SHALL fail rather than serve requests without credentials\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: Analyze endpoint accepts PCAP input\n128: \n129: - **GIVEN** a running service with valid LLM configuration\n130: - **WHEN** a client calls `POST /analyze` with either an uploaded PCAP file or a `pcap_path` form field\n131: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return a body matching `AnalyzeResponse` including `script`, `results`, and `report`\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer configuration surface\n136: \n137: The system SHALL read runtime configuration from environment variables for the OpenAI-compatible API, model selection, and AgentCube sandbox parameters.\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Defaults and overrides\n140: \n141: - **GIVEN** standard deployment environment variables\n142: - **WHEN** the service starts\n143: - **THEN** it SHALL use `OPENAI_API_BASE` defaulting to `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1`, `OPENAI_MODEL` defaulting to `Qwen/QwQ-32B`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` defaulting to `my-interpreter`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` defaulting to `default`, and `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` defaulting to `5`, while binding HTTP to `0.0.0.0:8000` as defined in the application\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer sandbox integration\n148: \n149: The system SHALL orchestrate PCAP analysis by planning and repairing scripts, executing them inside an AgentCube-backed sandbox via `SandboxRunner`, and aggregating results through reporter agents.\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: Sandbox runner executes commands\n152: \n153: - **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` constructed with interpreter name, namespace, and warmup duration\n154: - **WHEN** analysis logic invokes `run` with a shell command\n155: - **THEN** the runner SHALL execute the command in the remote sandbox context and SHALL return structured execution results for downstream LLM steps\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: File staging uses runner uploads\n158: \n159: - **GIVEN** a local PCAP path or bytes to analyze\n160: - **WHEN** the orchestration needs the artifact inside the sandbox workspace\n161: - **THEN** the system SHALL use `upload_file` or `upload_bytes` on `SandboxRunner` before executing analysis commands\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer container image\n166: \n167: The system SHALL build a container image that installs Python dependencies with `uv`, vendors the in-repo `agentcube` SDK copy, sets `PYTHONPATH`, exposes port 8000, and starts the FastAPI app via `uv run`.\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Image entrypoint\n170: \n171: - **GIVEN** the `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` build context\n172: - **WHEN** the container runs without overriding the command\n173: - **THEN** the default command SHALL be `uv run pcap_analyzer.py` with `PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"` and port `8000` exposed\n174: \n175: ---\n176: \n177: ### Requirement: PCAP analyzer Kubernetes deployment\n178: \n179: The system SHALL supply a `Deployment` manifest that runs the analyzer image with resource requests/limits and environment variables wired from a Secret and plain env for AgentCube and model endpoints.\n180: \n181: #### Scenario: Deployment wiring\n182: \n183: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` applied to the cluster\n184: - **WHEN** the workload becomes ready\n185: - **THEN** the pod SHALL run image `pcap-analyzer:latest` (pull `IfNotPresent`), listen on TCP 8000, request `cpu: 200m` / `memory: 100Mi` and limit `cpu: 1` / `memory: 1Gi`, mount `OPENAI_API_KEY` from Secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets` key `openai-api-key`, and set `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, and `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` as container environment variables\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: Process launch in cluster\n188: \n189: - **GIVEN** the deployment’s container specification\n190: - **WHEN** Kubernetes starts the container\n191: - **THEN** the command SHALL be `uv` with arguments `run pcap_analyzer.py`, matching local Docker behavior\n\n(End of file - total 191 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Integrations Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nNormative requirements for the AgentCube Dify plugin integration and the PCAP analyzer example that uses AgentCube code interpreters and Kubernetes sandboxes.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Dify plugin bootstrap and runtime\n\nThe system SHALL expose a Dify-compatible Python plugin whose process entry runs the framework runner with a configured maximum request timeout.\n\n#### Scenario: Plugin process starts\n\n- **GIVEN** the plugin package is installed with compatible `dify-plugin` and `agentcube-sdk` versions\n- **WHEN** the platform starts the plugin using the manifest-declared entrypoint\n- **THEN** the plugin SHALL execute `main` which runs `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` until the host stops it\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/integrations/spec.md","time":{"start":1775892360661,"end":1775892360682}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892360688,"sessionID":"ses_284915426ffebAopU0o9o5uo4G","part":{"id":"prt_d7b6eea45001Reat5pC2YcvRuI","messageID":"msg_d7b6ecbd7001LSeojddo3O3hZL","sessionID":"ses_284915426ffebAopU0o9o5uo4G","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-feb52eb0ca4848dcb17739bd52a264be","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/integrations/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/integrations/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Integrations — Design\n2: \n3: **AR-036 — Dify 插件集成**\n4: **Module**: integrations\n5: **Language**: Python\n6: **Size**: M\n7: \n8: Sources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/integrations/dify-plugin/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`.\n9: \n10: ## Overview\n11: \n12: This module defines the Dify plugin integration for AgentCube, enabling Dify AI platform users to leverage AgentCube code interpreters and agent runtimes as tools within their workflows. The integration consists of:\n13: \n14: 1. **Dify Plugin Package**: A Python plugin that exposes AgentCube code interpreter functionality as Dify-compatible tools\n15: 2. **PCAP Analyzer Example**: A FastAPI application demonstrating AgentCube sandbox integration with LangChain/LangGraph agents\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## Architecture\n20: \n21: ### Directory Structure\n22: \n23: ```\n24: integrations/\n25: ├── dify-plugin/\n26: │   ├── main.py                    # Plugin entry point\n27: │   ├── manifest.yaml              # Root plugin manifest\n28: │   ├── provider/\n29: │   │   ├── agentcube.yaml         # Provider descriptor\n30: │   │   └── agentcube.py           # Provider implementation\n31: │   ├── tools/\n32: │   │   ├── agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml  # Tool schema\n33: │   │   └── agentcube-code-interpreter.py    # Tool implementation\n34: │   ├── requirements.txt           # Python dependencies\n35: │   ├── GUIDE.md                   # User guide\n36: │   ├── README.md                  # Documentation\n37: │   ├── PRIVACY.md                 # Privacy policy\n38: │   ├── .difyignore                # Package ignore patterns\n39: │   └── icon.png                   # Light theme icon\n40: │   └── icon-dark.png              # Dark theme icon\n41: └── example/\n42:     └── pcap-analyzer/\n43:         ├── pcap_analyzer.py       # FastAPI application\n44:         ├── requirements.txt       # Dependencies\n45:         ├── Dockerfile             # Container image\n46:         ├── deployment.yaml        # Kubernetes deployment\n47:         └── README.md              # Documentation\n48: ```\n49: \n50: ### Plugin Architecture\n51: \n52: ```\n53: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n54: │                            Dify Platform                                       │\n55: ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n56: │                                                                               │\n57: │   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n58: │   │                    Dify Plugin Runtime                               │    │\n59: │   │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │    │\n60: │   │  │  Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()         │  │    │\n61: │   │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │    │\n62: │   │                            │                                         │    │\n63: │   │                            ▼                                         │    │\n64: │   │  ┌───────────────────┐    ┌───────────────────┐                     │    │\n65: │   │  │ Provider          │───▶│ Tool Registry     │                     │    │\n66: │   │  │ (agentcube.yaml)  │    │ (agentcube-code-  │                     │    │\n67: │   │  │                   │    │  interpreter.yaml)│                     │    │\n68: │   │  └───────────────────┘    └───────────────────┘                     │    │\n69: │   │                            │                                         │    │\n70: │   │                            ▼                                         │    │\n71: │   │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │    │\n72: │   │  │  AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool._invoke()                       │  │    │\n73: │   │  │  → execute() → CodeInterpreterClient → AgentCube Router       │  │    │\n74: │   │  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │    │\n75: │   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n76: │                                                                               │\n77: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n78: \n79: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n80: │                          AgentCube Backend                                     │\n81: ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n82: │                                                                               │\n83: │   ┌───────────────┐     ┌───────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────┐     │\n84: │   │    Router     │────▶│   Sandbox     │────▶│      PicoD            │     │\n85: │   │  (Session     │     │    Pod        │     │  (Code Execution)     │     │\n86: │   │   Routing)    │     │               │     │                       │     │\n87: │   └───────────────┘     └───────────────┘     └───────────────────────┘     │\n88: │          │                                                              │     │\n89: │          ▼                                                              │     │\n90: │   ┌───────────────┐                                                     │     │\n91: │   │ Workload      │                                                     │     │\n92: │   │  Manager      │                                                     │     │\n93: │   │ (Session CRUD)│                                                     │     │\n94: │   └───────────────┘                                                     │     │\n95: │                                                                               │\n96: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n97: ```\n98: \n99: ### PCAP Analyzer Architecture\n100: \n101: ```\n102: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n103: │                       PCAP Analyzer Service                                    │\n104: ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n105: │                                                                               │\n106: │   ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n107: │   │                         FastAPI Application                           │  │\n108: │   │                                                                        │  │\n109: │   │   POST /analyze                                                        │  │\n110: │   │   ├── pcap_file (UploadFile) OR pcap_path (Form)                      │  │\n111: │   │   ├── SandboxRunner.upload_file() / upload_bytes()                    │  │\n112: │   │   ├── _analyze_with_retries()                                         │  │\n113: │   │   │   ├── _plan_script() → PLANNER agent                              │  │\n114: │   │   │   ├── _execute_once_in_runner() → SandboxRunner.run()             │  │\n115: │   │   │   ├── _repair_script() → PLANNER agent (on failure)               │  │\n116: │   │   │   └── _report() → REPORTER agent                                  │  │\n117: │   │   └── AnalyzeResponse(script, results, report)                        │  │\n118: │   │                                                                        │  │\n119: │   └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n120: │                                    │                                         │\n121: │                                    ▼                                         │\n122: │   ┌───────────────────┐    ┌───────────────────┐    ┌───────────────────┐   │\n123: │   │ LangChain/LangGraph│    │   CodeInterpreter │    │   OpenAI-compatible│   │\n124: │   │   ReAct Agents     │───▶│     Client        │───▶│      LLM API       │   │\n125: │   │  (PLANNER/REPORTER)│    │   (SandboxRunner) │    │  (Qwen/QwQ-32B)   │   │\n126: │   └───────────────────┘    └───────────────────┘    └───────────────────┘   │\n127: │                                                                               │\n128: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n129: ```\n130: \n131: ### Data Flow\n132: \n133: ```\n134: ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n135: │   Dify User     │     │  Dify Platform  │     │  Dify Plugin    │\n136: │   Request       │────▶│   Workflow      │────▶│   Runtime       │\n137: └─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n138:                                                         │\n139:                                                         ▼\n140:                         ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n141:                         │  AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool._invoke()     │\n142:                         │  Parameters:                                │\n143:                         │  - router_url (required)                    │\n144:                         │  - workload_manager_url (required)          │\n145:                         │  - language (optional, default: python)     │\n146:                         │  - code / command                           │\n147:                         │  - session_id / session_reuse               │\n148:                         └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n149:                                                         │\n150:                                                         ▼\n151:                         ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n152:                         │  CodeInterpreterClient                      │\n153:                         │  1. Create session (ControlPlaneClient)     │\n154:                         │     POST /v1/code-interpreter               │\n155:                         │  2. Init data plane (CodeInterpreterData...)│\n156:                         │     base_url from router_url                │\n157:                         │  3. Execute code/command                    │\n158:                         │     POST api/execute                        │\n159:                         │  4. Return JSON result                      │\n160:                         └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n161:                                                         │\n162:                                                         ▼\n163:                         ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n164:                         │  Router → Sandbox Pod → PicoD               │\n165:                         │  JWT auth, session header routing           │\n166:                         │  Local execution in workspace               │\n167:                         └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n168:                                                         │\n169:                                                         ▼\n170:                         ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n171:                         │  Tool.create_json_message(result)           │\n172:                         │  → Dify workflow continues                  │\n173:                         └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n174: ```\n175: \n176: ---\n177: \n178: ## Data Structures\n179: \n180: ### Tool Parameter Types\n181: \n182: ```python\n183: from typing import Optional, Dict, Any\n184: from enum import Enum\n185: \n186: class LanguageType(str, Enum):\n187:     PYTHON = \"python\"\n188:     JAVASCRIPT = \"javascript\"\n189:     TYPESCRIPT = \"typescript\"\n190: \n191: class ToolParameters:\n192:     router_url: str              # Required - AgentCube Router endpoint\n193:     workload_manager_url: str    # Required - Workload Manager endpoint\n194:     language: LanguageType       # Optional - default: python\n195:     code: Optional[str]          # Optional - code to execute\n196:     command: Optional[str]       # Optional - shell command to run\n197:     session_id: Optional[str]    # Optional - existing session to reuse\n198:     session_reuse: bool          # Optional - default: False\n199:     code_interpreter_id: Optional[str]  # Optional - interpreter name\n200: ```\n201: \n202: ### Execution Result Schema\n203: \n204: ```python\n205: from typing import List, Dict, Any\n206: from pydantic import BaseModel\n207: \n208: class ExecutionResult(BaseModel):\n209:     stdout: str\n210:     stderr: str\n211:     exit_code: int\n212:     execution_time: float\n213:     files: Optional[List[Dict[str, Any]]] = None\n214: \n215: class AnalyzeResponse(BaseModel):\n216:     script: str\n217:     results: List[Dict[str, Any]]\n218:     report: str\n219: ```\n220: \n221: ### Session State\n222: \n223: ```python\n224: class SessionState:\n225:     session_id: str\n226:     code_interpreter_name: str\n227:     namespace: str\n228:     created_at: float\n229:     ttl: int\n230:     last_activity: float\n231:     metadata: Dict[str, Any]\n232: ```\n233: \n234: ---\n235: \n236: ## Dify plugin — file map\n237: \n238: | File | Role |\n239: |------|------|\n240: | `main.py` | `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` |\n241: | `manifest.yaml` | Root plugin manifest for Dify |\n242: | `provider/agentcube.yaml` | Tool provider identity + tool list + Python entry |\n243: | `provider/agentcube.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` |\n244: | `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | Tool parameter schema |\n245: | `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` |\n246: | `requirements.txt` | `dify-plugin` + `agentcube-sdk` pins |\n247: | `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore` | Docs / packaging |\n248: \n249: ## `manifest.yaml` structure (exact top-level keys)\n250: \n251: From source:\n252: \n253: - `version`: `0.0.2`\n254: - `type`: `plugin`\n255: - `author`: `volcano-sh`\n256: - `name`: `agentcube`\n257: - `label`: map `en_US`, `ja_JP`, `zh_Hans`, `pt_BR` → `Agentcube`\n258: - `description`: multilingual strings (AgentCube description)\n259: - `icon`: `icon.png`\n260: - `icon_dark`: `icon-dark.png`\n261: - `resource`: `memory`, `permission` subtree (`tool`, `model`, `endpoint`, `app`, `storage` flags and sizes)\n262: - `plugins.tools`: list `[provider/agentcube.yaml]`\n263: - `meta`: `version`, `arch` (`amd64`, `arm64`), `runner` (`language: python`, `version: \"3.12\"`, `entrypoint: main`), `minimum_dify_version: null`\n264: - `created_at`, `privacy`, `repo`, `verified`\n265: \n266: ## `provider/agentcube.yaml` structure\n267: \n268: - `identity`: `author`, `name`, `label` (multilingual), `description` (multilingual), `icon`\n269: - Commented `oauth_schema` block (not active)\n270: - `tools`: list `[tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml]`\n271: - `extra.python.source`: `provider/agentcube.py`\n272: \n273: ## Tool definition (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`)\n274: \n275: - `identity.name`: `agentcube-code-interpreter`\n276: - `identity.author`: `agentcube`\n277: - `identity.label` / `description` (human + llm strings)\n278: - `parameters` (each has `name`, `type`, `required`, `label`, `human_description`, `llm_description`, `form`):\n279: \n280: | name | type | required | form | notes |\n281: |------|------|----------|------|-------|\n282: | `router_url` | string | true | form | |\n283: | `workload_manager_url` | string | true | form | |\n284: | `language` | select | false | llm | options: `python`, `javascript`, `typescript` |\n285: | `code` | string | false | llm | |\n286: | `command` | string | false | llm | |\n287: | `session_id` | string | false | llm | |\n288: | `session_reuse` | boolean | false | llm | |\n289: | `code_interpreter_id` | string | false | llm | |\n290: \n291: - `extra.python.source`: `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`\n292: \n293: ## Provider implementation (`provider/agentcube.py`)\n294: \n295: ```python\n296: from dify_plugin import ToolProvider\n297: from dify_plugin.errors.tool import ToolProviderCredentialValidationError\n298: \n299: class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider(ToolProvider):\n300:     def _validate_credentials(self, credentials: dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n301:         try:\n302:             \"\"\" IMPLEMENT YOUR VALIDATION HERE \"\"\"\n303:         except Exception as e:\n304:             raise ToolProviderCredentialValidationError(str(e))\n305: ```\n306: \n307: (OAuth helper methods are present only as comments.)\n308: \n309: ## Tool implementation (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`)\n310: \n311: ```python\n312: from collections.abc import Generator\n313: from typing import Any\n314: from dify_plugin import Tool\n315: from dify_plugin.entities.tool import ToolInvokeMessage\n316: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n317: \n318: class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool(Tool):\n319:     def _invoke(self, tool_parameters: dict[str, Any]) -> Generator[ToolInvokeMessage]:\n320:         result = self.execute(**tool_parameters)\n321:         yield self.create_json_message(result)\n322: \n323:     def execute(\n324:         self,\n325:         router_url=None,\n326:         workload_manager_url=None,\n327:         language=\"python\",\n328:         code_interpreter_id=None,\n329:         session_id=None,\n330:         code=None,\n331:         command=None,\n332:         session_reuse=False,\n333:         **kwargs\n334:     ): ...\n335: ```\n336: \n337: ## Plugin dependencies (`integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`)\n338: \n339: ```\n340: dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0\n341: agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10\n342: ```\n343: \n344: ## PCAP analyzer — application structure (`example/pcap-analyzer/`)\n345: \n346: | File | Role |\n347: |------|------|\n348: | `pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI app, agents, sandbox runner, analysis orchestration, `uvicorn` entry |\n349: | `requirements.txt` | FastAPI, uvicorn, LangChain / LangGraph stack, multipart, etc. |\n350: | `Dockerfile` | `uv` base image, installs reqs, copies `sdk-python/agentcube` + `pcap_analyzer.py` |\n351: | `deployment.yaml` | K8s Deployment + env for OpenAI-compatible API and AgentCube URLs |\n352: | `README.md` | Documentation |\n353: \n354: ## FastAPI application (`pcap_analyzer.py`)\n355: \n356: ### Globals / config (selected)\n357: \n358: | Name | Source | Default / value |\n359: |------|--------|-----------------|\n360: | `API_KEY` | `OPENAI_API_KEY` | required at startup |\n361: | `API_BASE_URL` | `OPENAI_API_BASE` | `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1` |\n362: | `MODEL_NAME` | `OPENAI_MODEL` | `Qwen/QwQ-32B` |\n363: | `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` | env | `my-interpreter` |\n364: | `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` | env | `default` |\n365: | `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` | env | `5` |\n366: | `SERVER_HOST` | constant | `0.0.0.0` |\n367: | `SERVER_PORT` | constant | `8000` |\n368: | `SERVER_RELOAD` | constant | `True` |\n369: \n370: ### Core classes / functions\n371: \n372: ```python\n373: class SandboxRunner:\n374:     def __init__(self, name: str = \"my-interpreter\", namespace: str = \"default\", warmup_sec: int = 5): ...\n375:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> bool: ...\n376:     def upload_bytes(self, data: bytes, remote_path: str) -> bool: ...\n377:     def run(self, command: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n378:     def stop(self): ...\n379: \n380: def build_react_agent(llm, system_prompt: str): ...\n381: def invoke_react_agent(agent, user_text: str) -> str: ...\n382: def build_planner_agent(llm): ...\n383: def build_reporter_agent(llm): ...\n384: \n385: def _plan_script(agent, pcap_local_path: str) -> str: ...\n386: def _repair_script(agent, prev_script: str, results: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> str: ...\n387: def _execute_once_in_runner(runner: SandboxRunner, pcap_local_path: str, script: str) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n388: def _analyze_with_retries(..., max_retries: int = 2) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n389: def _report(agent, results: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> str: ...\n390: \n391: class AnalyzeResponse(BaseModel):\n392:     script: str\n393:     results: List[Dict[str, Any]]\n394:     report: str\n395: \n396: app = FastAPI(title=\"PCAP Analyzer — Env-Only Config\")\n397: ```\n398: \n399: ### FastAPI endpoints\n400: \n401: | Method | Path | Signature / behavior |\n402: |--------|------|----------------------|\n403: | (event) | startup | `on_startup()` → builds `ChatOpenAI`, `PLANNER`, `REPORTER`; fails if no API key |\n404: | `POST` | `/analyze` | `async def analyze_endpoint(pcap_file: UploadFile = File(None), pcap_path: str = Form(None))` → `response_model=AnalyzeResponse` |\n405: \n406: ### Imports of note\n407: \n408: ```python\n409: from fastapi import FastAPI, UploadFile, File, Form, HTTPException\n410: from pydantic import BaseModel\n411: import uvicorn\n412: from langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI\n413: from langgraph.prebuilt import create_react_agent\n414: from langchain_core.messages import HumanMessage, AIMessage\n415: from agentcube.code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n416: from agentcube.exceptions import CommandExecutionError\n417: ```\n418: \n419: ## Kubernetes deployment (`deployment.yaml`)\n420: \n421: - `Deployment` `pcap-analyzer` in `namespace: default`\n422: - Container `pcap-analyzer`, image `pcap-analyzer:latest`, `imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n423: - Container port `8000` TCP\n424: - Resources: requests `cpu: 200m`, `memory: 100Mi`; limits `cpu: 1`, `memory: 1Gi`\n425: - Env: `OPENAI_API_KEY` from secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets` key `openai-api-key`; `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC`\n426: - Command: `[\"uv\"]`, args: `[\"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n427: \n428: ## Dockerfile highlights\n429: \n430: - Base: `ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim`\n431: - `uv venv` + `uv pip install -r requirements.txt`\n432: - Copies `sdk-python/agentcube` → `./agentcube/`, `pcap_analyzer.py` → `./`\n433: - `ENV PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"`, exposes `8000`\n434: - `CMD [\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n435: \n436: ## PCAP example Python dependencies (`example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt`)\n437: \n438: Pinned packages include: `fastapi==0.120.0`, `uvicorn==0.38.0`, `langchain==1.0.2`, `langchain-classic==1.0.0`, `langchain-community==0.4.1`, `langchain-core==1.0.1`, `langchain-openai==1.0.1`, `langchain-text-splitters==1.0.0`, `langgraph==1.0.1`, `langgraph-checkpoint==3.0.0`, `langgraph-prebuilt==1.0.1`, `langgraph-sdk==0.2.9`, `langsmith==0.4.38`, `paramiko==4.0.0`, `python-multipart==0.0.20`\n439: \n440: *(The Dockerfile vendors `agentcube` from the monorepo copy; it is not listed in this `requirements.txt`.)*\n441: \n442: ---\n443: \n444: ## Error Handling\n445: \n446: ### Error Categories\n447: \n448: | Category | Description | Recovery Action |\n449: |----------|-------------|-----------------|\n450: | `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` | Invalid credentials provided | Raise with descriptive message |\n451: | `CommandExecutionError` | Remote command failed (non-zero exit) | Include exit_code, stderr in result |\n452: | `SessionError` | Session creation/deletion failed | Log warning, return error JSON |\n453: | `DataPlaneError` | Router/sandbox communication failed | Retry with exponential backoff |\n454: | `ValueError` | Missing required parameters (router_url) | Raise before execution attempt |\n455: \n456: ### Plugin Error Handling Pattern\n457: \n458: ```python\n459: from dify_plugin.errors.tool import ToolProviderCredentialValidationError\n460: from agentcube.exceptions import CommandExecutionError, SessionError\n461: \n462: class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool(Tool):\n463:     def _invoke(self, tool_parameters: dict[str, Any]) -> Generator[ToolInvokeMessage]:\n464:         try:\n465:             if not tool_parameters.get(\"router_url\"):\n466:                 yield self.create_json_message({\n467:                     \"error\": \"router_url is required\",\n468:                     \"error_type\": \"ValidationError\"\n469:                 })\n470:                 return\n471:             \n472:             result = self.execute(**tool_parameters)\n473:             yield self.create_json_message(result)\n474:         except CommandExecutionError as e:\n475:             yield self.create_json_message({\n476:                 \"error\": str(e),\n477:                 \"error_type\": \"CommandExecutionError\",\n478:                 \"exit_code\": e.exit_code,\n479:                 \"stderr\": e.stderr\n480:             })\n481:         except SessionError as e:\n482:             yield self.create_json_message({\n483:                 \"error\": str(e),\n484:                 \"error_type\": \"SessionError\"\n485:             })\n486:         except Exception as e:\n487:             yield self.create_json_message({\n488:                 \"error\": str(e),\n489:                 \"error_type\": \"UnexpectedError\"\n490:             })\n491: ```\n492: \n493: ### PCAP Analyzer Error Handling\n494: \n495: ```python\n496: from fastapi import HTTPException\n497: \n498: @app.on_event(\"startup\")\n499: async def on_startup():\n500:     if not API_KEY:\n501:         raise RuntimeError(\"OPENAI_API_KEY is required at startup\")\n502: \n503: @app.post(\"/analyze\", response_model=AnalyzeResponse)\n504: async def analyze_endpoint(\n505:     pcap_file: UploadFile = File(None),\n506:     pcap_path: str = Form(None)\n507: ):\n508:     if not pcap_file and not pcap_path:\n509:         raise HTTPException(status_code=400, detail=\"Either pcap_file or pcap_path required\")\n510:     \n511:     try:\n512:         runner = SandboxRunner(\n513:             name=CODEINTERPRETER_NAME,\n514:             namespace=SANDBOX_NAMESPACE,\n515:             warmup_sec=int(SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC)\n516:         )\n517:         result = _analyze_with_retries(runner, pcap_file or pcap_path)\n518:         return result\n519:     except CommandExecutionError as e:\n520:         raise HTTPException(status_code=500, detail=f\"Sandbox error: {e.stderr}\")\n521:     finally:\n522:         runner.stop()\n523: ```\n524: \n525: ### Error Response Schema\n526: \n527: ```python\n528: class ErrorResponse(BaseModel):\n529:     error: str\n530:     error_type: str\n531:     exit_code: Optional[int] = None\n532:     stderr: Optional[str] = None\n533:     retry_count: Optional[int] = None\n534: ```\n535: \n536: ---\n537: \n538: ## Testing Strategy\n539: \n540: ### Unit Tests\n541: \n542: #### Tool Provider Tests\n543: \n544: ```python\n545: import pytest\n546: from unittest.mock import Mock, patch\n547: from dify_plugin.errors.tool import ToolProviderCredentialValidationError\n548: \n549: def test_provider_validate_credentials_success():\n550:     provider = AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider()\n551:     credentials = {\"router_url\": \"http://router:8080\", \"workload_manager_url\": \"http://wm:8080\"}\n552:     provider._validate_credentials(credentials)\n553:     # Should not raise\n554: \n555: def test_provider_validate_credentials_missing_url():\n556:     provider = AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider()\n557:     credentials = {\"router_url\": \"\", \"workload_manager_url\": \"http://wm:8080\"}\n558:     with pytest.raises(ToolProviderCredentialValidationError):\n559:         provider._validate_credentials(credentials)\n560: ```\n561: \n562: #### Tool Invocation Tests\n563: \n564: ```python\n565: def test_tool_invoke_missing_router_url():\n566:     tool = AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool()\n567:     messages = list(tool._invoke({\"workload_manager_url\": \"http://wm:8080\"}))\n568:     result = json.loads(messages[0].message)\n569:     assert result[\"error_type\"] == \"ValidationError\"\n570:     assert \"router_url\" in result[\"error\"]\n571: \n572: def test_tool_invoke_code_execution():\n573:     tool = AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool()\n574:     with patch.object(tool, 'execute') as mock_execute:\n575:         mock_execute.return_value = {\"stdout\": \"hello\", \"stderr\": \"\", \"exit_code\": 0}\n576:         messages = list(tool._invoke({\n577:             \"router_url\": \"http://router:8080\",\n578:             \"workload_manager_url\": \"http://wm:8080\",\n579:             \"code\": \"print('hello')\"\n580:         }))\n581:         result = json.loads(messages[0].message)\n582:         assert result[\"exit_code\"] == 0\n583:         assert result[\"stdout\"] == \"hello\"\n584: \n585: def test_tool_invoke_command_failure():\n586:     tool = AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool()\n587:     with patch.object(tool, 'execute') as mock_execute:\n588:         mock_execute.side_effect = CommandExecutionError(\n589:             exit_code=1, stderr=\"error output\", command=\"ls /nonexistent\"\n590:         )\n591:         messages = list(tool._invoke({\n592:             \"router_url\": \"http://router:8080\",\n593:             \"workload_manager_url\": \"http://wm:8080\",\n594:             \"command\": \"ls /nonexistent\"\n595:         }))\n596:         result = json.loads(messages[0].message)\n597:         assert result[\"error_type\"] == \"CommandExecutionError\"\n598:         assert result[\"exit_code\"] == 1\n599: ```\n600: \n601: #### Session Reuse Tests\n602: \n603: ```python\n604: def test_tool_session_reuse():\n605:     tool = AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool()\n606:     with patch('agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient') as mock_client:\n607:         mock_client.return_value.session_id = \"existing-session-123\"\n608:         mock_client.return_value.execute_command.return_value = \"output\"\n609:         \n610:         messages = list(tool._invoke({\n611:             \"router_url\": \"http://router:8080\",\n612:             \"workload_manager_url\": \"http://wm:8080\",\n613:             \"session_id\": \"existing-session-123\",\n614:             \"session_reuse\": True,\n615:             \"command\": \"echo test\"\n616:         }))\n617:         # Verify client was initialized with existing session_id\n618:         mock_client.assert_called_with(session_id=\"existing-session-123\")\n619: ```\n620: \n621: #### PCAP Analyzer Tests\n622: \n623: ```python\n624: def test_analyze_endpoint_missing_input():\n625:     client = TestClient(app)\n626:     response = client.post(\"/analyze\")\n627:     assert response.status_code == 400\n628: \n629: def test_analyze_endpoint_with_file():\n630:     client = TestClient(app)\n631:     pcap_content = b\"mock pcap data\"\n632:     with patch('pcap_analyzer._analyze_with_retries') as mock_analyze:\n633:         mock_analyze.return_value = {\n634:             \"script\": \"# analysis script\",\n635:             \"results\": [{\"stdout\": \"ok\"}],\n636:             \"report\": \"Analysis complete\"\n637:         }\n638:         response = client.post(\n639:             \"/analyze\",\n640:             files={\"pcap_file\": (\"test.pcap\", pcap_content)}\n641:         )\n642:         assert response.status_code == 200\n643:         assert response.json()[\"report\"] == \"Analysis complete\"\n644: \n645: def test_startup_without_api_key():\n646:     with patch.dict(os.environ, {\"OPENAI_API_KEY\": \"\"}):\n647:         with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n648:             on_startup()\n649: ```\n650: \n651: ### Integration Tests\n652: \n653: #### End-to-End Plugin Test\n654: \n655: ```python\n656: @pytest.mark.integration\n657: def test_plugin_e2e_code_execution():\n658:     \"\"\"Test full plugin invocation with live AgentCube backend.\"\"\"\n659:     tool = AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool()\n660:     messages = list(tool._invoke({\n661:         \"router_url\": os.environ[\"ROUTER_URL\"],\n662:         \"workload_manager_url\": os.environ[\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\"],\n663:         \"language\": \"python\",\n664:         \"code\": \"import sys; print(sys.version)\"\n665:     }))\n666:     result = json.loads(messages[0].message)\n667:     assert result[\"exit_code\"] == 0\n668:     assert \"3.12\" in result[\"stdout\"]  # Python version check\n669: ```\n670: \n671: #### PCAP Analyzer E2E Test\n672: \n673: ```python\n674: @pytest.mark.integration\n675: def test_pcap_analyzer_e2e():\n676:     \"\"\"Test PCAP analyzer with real sandbox.\"\"\"\n677:     client = TestClient(app)\n678:     pcap_path = \"tests/fixtures/sample.pcap\"\n679:     \n680:     response = client.post(\n681:         \"/analyze\",\n682:         data={\"pcap_path\": pcap_path}\n683:     )\n684:     assert response.status_code == 200\n685:     data = response.json()\n686:     assert \"script\" in data\n687:     assert \"results\" in data\n688:     assert \"report\" in data\n689: ```\n690: \n691: ### Test Configuration\n692: \n693: ```python\n694: # tests/conftest.py\n695: import pytest\n696: from unittest.mock import patch\n697: \n698: @pytest.fixture\n699: def mock_code_interpreter_client():\n700:     with patch('agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient') as mock:\n701:         client = mock.return_value\n702:         client.execute_command.return_value = \"mock output\"\n703:         client.run_code.return_value = \"mock output\"\n704:         client.session_id = \"test-session-123\"\n705:         yield client\n706: \n707: @pytest.fixture\n708: def mock_sandbox_runner():\n709:     with patch('pcap_analyzer.SandboxRunner') as mock:\n710:         runner = mock.return_value\n711:         runner.run.return_value = {\"stdout\": \"ok\", \"stderr\": \"\", \"exit_code\": 0}\n712:         runner.upload_file.return_value = True\n713:         yield runner\n714: ```\n715: \n716: ---\n717: \n718: ## Metrics\n719: \n720: ### Prometheus Metrics\n721: \n722: ```python\n723: from prometheus_client import Counter, Histogram, Gauge\n724: \n725: TOOL_INVOCATIONS = Counter(\n726:     'agentcube_dify_tool_invocations_total',\n727:     'Total tool invocations',\n728:     ['tool_name', 'language', 'status']\n729: )\n730: \n731: EXECUTION_DURATION = Histogram(\n732:     'agentcube_dify_execution_duration_seconds',\n733:     'Code execution duration',\n734:     ['language'],\n735:     buckets=[0.1, 0.5, 1, 5, 10, 30, 60, 120]\n736: )\n737: \n738: SESSION_CREATIONS = Counter(\n739:     'agentcube_dify_session_creations_total',\n740:     'Session creation count',\n741:     ['session_type']  # 'new' or 'reuse'\n742: )\n743: \n744: ACTIVE_SESSIONS = Gauge(\n745:     'agentcube_dify_active_sessions',\n746:     'Currently active sessions'\n747: )\n748: \n749: PCAP_ANALYSIS_DURATION = Histogram(\n750:     'agentcube_pcap_analysis_duration_seconds',\n751:     'PCAP analysis total duration',\n752:     buckets=[1, 5, 10, 30, 60, 120, 300]\n753: )\n754: ```\n755: \n756: ### Metric Usage in Tool\n757: \n758: ```python\n759: class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool(Tool):\n760:     def _invoke(self, tool_parameters):\n761:         start_time = time.time()\n762:         language = tool_parameters.get(\"language\", \"python\")\n763:         session_type = \"reuse\" if tool_parameters.get(\"session_reuse\") else \"new\"\n764:         \n765:         try:\n766:             result = self.execute(**tool_parameters)\n767:             status = \"success\" if result.get(\"exit_code\") == 0 else \"error\"\n768:             \n769:             TOOL_INVOCATIONS.labels(\n770:                 tool_name=\"agentcube-code-interpreter\",\n771:                 language=language,\n772:                 status=status\n773:             ).inc()\n774:             \n775:             EXECUTION_DURATION.labels(language=language).observe(\n776:                 time.time() - start_time\n777:             )\n778:             \n779:             SESSION_CREATIONS.labels(session_type=session_type).inc()\n780:             \n781:             yield self.create_json_message(result)\n782:         except Exception as e:\n783:             TOOL_INVOCATIONS.labels(\n784:                 tool_name=\"agentcube-code-interpreter\",\n785:                 language=language,\n786:                 status=\"exception\"\n787:             ).inc()\n788:             yield self.create_json_message({\"error\": str(e)})\n789: ```\n790: \n791: ---\n792: \n793: ## Configuration\n794: \n795: ### Environment Variables\n796: \n797: | Variable | Plugin | PCAP Analyzer | Default |\n798: |----------|--------|---------------|---------|\n799: | `ROUTER_URL` | Required | Required | - |\n800: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Required | Required | - |\n801: | `MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT` | Plugin entry | - | `120` |\n802: | `OPENAI_API_KEY` | - | Required | - |\n803: | `OPENAI_API_BASE` | - | Optional | `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1` |\n804: | `OPENAI_MODEL` | - | Optional | `Qwen/QwQ-32B` |\n805: | `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` | - | Optional | `my-interpreter` |\n806: | `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` | - | Optional | `default` |\n807: | `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` | - | Optional | `5` |\n808: \n809: ### Kubernetes Configuration\n810: \n811: ```yaml\n812: apiVersion: v1\n813: kind: Secret\n814: metadata:\n815:   name: pcap-analyzer-secrets\n816: type: Opaque\n817: data:\n818:   openai-api-key: <base64-encoded-key>\n819: ---\n820: apiVersion: apps/v1\n821: kind: Deployment\n822: metadata:\n823:   name: pcap-analyzer\n824: spec:\n825:   template:\n826:     spec:\n827:       containers:\n828:       - name: pcap-analyzer\n829:         image: pcap-analyzer:latest\n830:         env:\n831:         - name: OPENAI_API_KEY\n832:           valueFrom:\n833:             secretKeyRef:\n834:               name: pcap-analyzer-secrets\n835:               key: openai-api-key\n836:         - name: ROUTER_URL\n837:           value: \"http://agentcube-router:8080\"\n838:         - name: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n839:           value: \"http://workload-manager:8080\"\n840: ```\n841: \n842: ---\n843: \n844: ## Build Configuration\n845: \n846: ### Plugin Package Build\n847: \n848: ```bash\n849: # Create plugin package\n850: cd integrations/dify-plugin\n851: pip install dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0\n852: dify-plugin package .\n853: # Output: agentcube.difypkg\n854: ```\n855: \n856: ### Docker Build (PCAP Analyzer)\n857: \n858: ```dockerfile\n859: FROM ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim\n860: \n861: WORKDIR /app\n862: \n863: # Install dependencies\n864: RUN uv venv && uv pip install -r requirements.txt\n865: \n866: # Vendor SDK from monorepo\n867: COPY sdk-python/agentcube ./agentcube/\n868: COPY example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py ./\n869: \n870: ENV PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"\n871: EXPOSE 8000\n872: \n873: CMD [\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]\n874: ```\n875: \n876: ### Makefile Targets\n877: \n878: ```makefile\n879: .PHONY: build-plugin build-pcap-analyzer package-plugin\n880: \n881: build-plugin:\n882: \tcd integrations/dify-plugin && pip install -r requirements.txt\n883: \n884: build-pcap-analyzer:\n885: \tdocker build -t pcap-analyzer:latest -f integrations/example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile .\n886: \n887: package-plugin:\n888: \tcd integrations/dify-plugin && dify-plugin package .\n889: \n890: test-integrations:\n891: \tpytest integrations/tests/ -v\n892: ```\n893: \n894: ---\n895: \n896: ## Implementation Checklist\n897: \n898: ### Dify Plugin\n899: \n900: - [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/main.py` - Plugin entry point\n901: - [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml` - Root manifest\n902: - [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.yaml` - Provider descriptor\n903: - [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py` - Provider implementation\n904: - [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` - Tool schema\n905: - [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` - Tool implementation\n906: - [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt` - Dependencies\n907: - [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/GUIDE.md` - User guide\n908: - [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/README.md` - Documentation\n909: - [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/PRIVACY.md` - Privacy policy\n910: - [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/.difyignore` - Package ignore rules\n911: - [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/icon.png` - Light theme icon\n912: - [ ] `integrations/dify-plugin/icon-dark.png` - Dark theme icon\n913: \n914: ### PCAP Analyzer Example\n915: \n916: - [ ] `integrations/example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` - FastAPI app\n917: - [ ] `integrations/example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt` - Dependencies\n918: - [ ] `integrations/example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` - Container build\n919: - [ ] `integrations/example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` - Kubernetes manifest\n920: - [ ] `integrations/example/pcap-analyzer/README.md` - Documentation\n921: \n922: ### Testing\n923: \n924: - [ ] Unit tests for provider credential validation\n925: - [ ] Unit tests for tool invocation\n926: - [ ] Unit tests for session reuse logic\n927: - [ ] Unit tests for PCAP analyzer endpoints\n928: - [ ] Integration tests with mock backend\n929: - [ ] E2E tests with live AgentCube backend\n930: \n931: ### CI/CD\n932: \n933: - [ ] GitHub workflow for plugin packaging\n934: - [ ] GitHub workflow for PCAP analyzer Docker build\n935: - [ ] GitHub workflow for integration tests\n936: - [ ] Dify marketplace publishing automation\n937: \n938: ---\n939: \n940: ## Dependencies\n941: \n942: ### Dify Plugin Dependencies\n943: \n944: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n945: |---------|---------|---------|\n946: | `dify-plugin` | `>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` | Dify plugin framework |\n947: | `agentcube-sdk` | `>=0.0.10` | AgentCube Python client |\n948: | `requests` | (via agentcube-sdk) | HTTP client |\n949: | `PyJWT` | `>=2.0.0` (via agentcube-sdk) | JWT handling |\n950: | `cryptography` | (via agentcube-sdk) | Crypto utilities |\n951: \n952: ### PCAP Analyzer Dependencies\n953: \n954: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n955: |---------|---------|---------|\n956: | `fastapi` | `==0.120.0` | Web framework |\n957: | `uvicorn` | `==0.38.0` | ASGI server |\n958: | `langchain` | `==1.0.2` | LLM framework |\n959: | `langchain-openai` | `==1.0.1` | OpenAI integration |\n960: | `langgraph` | `==1.0.1` | Agent orchestration |\n961: | `langgraph-prebuilt` | `==1.0.1` | Prebuilt agent patterns |\n962: | `python-multipart` | `==0.0.20` | File upload handling |\n963: | `paramiko` | `==4.0.0` | SSH client |\n964: | `agentcube` | (vendored) | AgentCube SDK |\n965: \n966: ### External Service Dependencies\n967: \n968: | Service | Purpose | Protocol |\n969: |---------|---------|----------|\n970: | AgentCube Router | Session routing | HTTP |\n971: | Workload Manager | Session CRUD | HTTP |\n972: | Sandbox Pod (PicoD) | Code execution | HTTP |\n973: | OpenAI-compatible API | LLM inference | HTTP |\n974: | Kubernetes | Container orchestration | API |\n975: \n976: ---\n977: \n978: ## API Contracts Summary\n979: \n980: ### Dify Plugin API\n981: \n982: | Endpoint | Method | Purpose |\n983: |----------|--------|---------|\n984: | (internal) | `_validate_credentials` | Provider credential check |\n985: | (internal) | `_invoke` | Tool execution entry |\n986: | Router `/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{name}/invocations/api/execute` | POST | Code/command execution |\n987: | Router `/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{name}/invocations/api/files` | POST/GET | File operations |\n988: | Workload Manager `/v1/code-interpreter` | POST | Session creation |\n989: | Workload Manager `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{id}` | DELETE | Session deletion |\n990: \n991: ### PCAP Analyzer API\n992: \n993: | Endpoint | Method | Request | Response |\n994: |----------|--------|---------|----------|\n995: | `/analyze` | POST | `pcap_file: UploadFile` or `pcap_path: str` | `AnalyzeResponse` |\n996: | `/health` | GET | - | `{status: \"ok\"}` |\n997: \n998: ---\n999: \n1000: ## Security Considerations\n1001: \n1002: ### Plugin Security\n1003: \n1004: - Credentials validated before execution\n1005: - Session IDs used for request routing\n1006: - JWT tokens handled by Router (not SDK)\n1007: - No secrets in plugin package\n1008: \n1009: ### PCAP Analyzer Security\n1010: \n1011: - API key required at startup (fail-fast)\n1012: - Secrets mounted from Kubernetes Secret\n1013: - Sandbox isolation via AgentCube\n1014: - No direct filesystem access\n1015: \n1016: ### Kubernetes RBAC\n1017: \n1018: ```yaml\n1019: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n1020: kind: Role\n1021: metadata:\n1022:   name: pcap-analyzer\n1023: rules:\n1024: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n1025:   resources: [\"codeinterpreters\"]\n1026:   verbs: [\"get\", \"create\", \"delete\"]\n1027: ```\n\n(End of file - total 1027 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Integrations — Design\n\n**AR-036 — Dify 插件集成**\n**Module**: integrations\n**Language**: Python\n**Size**: M\n\nSources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/integrations/dify-plugin/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`.\n\n## Overview\n\nThis module defines the Dify plugin integration for AgentCube, enabling Dify AI platform users to leverage AgentCube code interpreters and agent runtimes as tools within their workflows. The integration consists of:\n\n1. **Dify Plugin Package**: A Python plugin that exposes AgentCube code interpreter functionality as Dify-compatible tools\n2. **PCAP Analyzer Example**: A FastAPI application demonstrating AgentCube sandbox integration with LangChain/LangGraph agents\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/integrations/design.md","time":{"start":1775892360660,"end":1775892360685}}}}
