lds\n33:   - `readiness_probe_path: str = Field(\"\", description=\"Path for readiness probe\")`\n34:   - `readiness_probe_port: int = Field(8080, description=\"Port for readiness probe\")`\n35:   - Purpose: Configure health check endpoints for AgentRuntime CR\n36:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n37:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_metadata_service.py::TestAgentMetadata::test_readiness_probe_fields -v`\n38: \n39: ### Phase 2: KubernetesProvider Class (ST-2)\n40: \n41: - [ ] **T2.1**: Create `k8s_provider.py` skeleton\n42:   - Import: `kubernetes`, `time`, `re`, `Path`, `Dict`, `Any`, `Optional`\n43:   - Define constants: `NODE_PORT_MIN=30000`, `NODE_PORT_MAX=32767`, `DEFAULT_TIMEOUT=120`, `POLL_INTERVAL=2`\n44:   - Define class: `class KubernetesProvider`\n45:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n46:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.services.k8s_provider import KubernetesProvider\"`\n47: \n48: - [ ] **T2.2**: Implement `KubernetesProvider.__init__()`\n49:   - Parameters: `namespace: str = \"default\"`, `verbose: bool = False`, `kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None`\n50:   - Load kubeconfig: `kubernetes.config.load_kube_config(config_file=kubeconfig)` or default\n51:   - Initialize APIs: `self.apps_api = kubernetes.client.AppsV1Api()`, `self.core_api = kubernetes.client.CoreV1Api()`\n52:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n53:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_init -v`\n54: \n55: - [ ] **T2.3**: Implement `_sanitize_name()` method\n56:   - Convert name to lowercase DNS-compliant (max 63 chars)\n57:   - Pattern: `re.sub(r\"[^a-z0-9-]\", \"-\", name.lower())`\n58:   - Truncate to 63 chars, remove leading/trailing `-`\n59:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n60:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_sanitize_name -v`\n61: \n62: - [ ] **T2.4**: Implement `_ensure_namespace()` method\n63:   - Check if namespace exists via `self.core_api.read_namespace()`\n64:   - Create if not exists: `self.core_api.create_namespace()`\n65:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n66:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_ensure_namespace -v`\n67: \n68: - [ ] **T2.5**: Implement `_create_deployment()` method\n69:   - Build Deployment body with: `apiVersion`, `kind`, `metadata`, `spec`\n70:   - Include: `replicas`, `selector`, `template` with container spec\n71:   - Container: `name`, `image`, `ports`, `env` from env_vars\n72:   - Call `self.apps_api.create_namespaced_deployment()`\n73:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n74:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_create_deployment -v`\n75: \n76: - [ ] **T2.6**: Implement `_create_service()` method\n77:   - Build NodePort Service body with: `apiVersion`, `kind`, `metadata`, `spec`\n78:   - Type: `NodePort`, selector matching deployment labels\n79:   - Port mapping: `port`, `targetPort`, optional `nodePort`\n80:   - Call `self.core_api.create_namespaced_service()`\n81:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n82:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_create_service -v`\n83: \n84: - [ ] **T2.7**: Implement `wait_for_deployment_ready()` method\n85:   - Poll `self.apps_api.read_namespaced_deployment()` status\n86:   - Check `deployment.status.available_replicas == deployment.spec.replicas`\n87:   - Sleep `POLL_INTERVAL` seconds between checks\n88:   - Raise `TimeoutError` if `timeout` exceeded\n89:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n90:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_wait_for_ready -v`\n91: \n92: - [ ] **T2.8**: Implement `deploy_agent()` main method\n93:   - Parameters: `agent_name`, `image_url`, `port`, `entrypoint`, `replicas`, `node_port`, `env_vars`\n94:   - Validate `node_port` in range 30000-32767 if provided\n95:   - Call `_ensure_namespace()`, `_sanitize_name()`\n96:   - Call `_create_deployment()`, `_create_service()`\n97:   - Call `wait_for_deployment_ready()`\n98:   - Return deployment info dict\n99:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n100:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_deploy_agent -v`\n101: \n102: - [ ] **T2.9**: Implement `get_agent_status()` method\n103:   - Read Deployment: `self.apps_api.read_namespaced_deployment()`\n104:   - Read Service: `self.core_api.read_namespaced_service()`\n105:   - Return combined status dict\n106:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n107:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_get_status -v`\n108: \n109: - [ ] **T2.10**: Implement `delete_agent()` method\n110:   - Delete Deployment: `self.apps_api.delete_namespaced_deployment()`\n111:   - Delete Service: `self.core_api.delete_namespaced_service()`\n112:   - Return deletion status dict\n113:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n114:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py::TestKubernetesProvider::test_delete_agent -v`\n115: \n116: ### Phase 3: AgentCubeProvider Class (ST-3)\n117: \n118: - [ ] **T3.1**: Create `agentcube_provider.py` skeleton\n119:   - Import: `kubernetes`, `re`, `Dict`, `Any`, `Optional`\n120:   - Define constants: `CR_GROUP=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`, `CR_VERSION=\"v1alpha1\"`, `CR_PLURAL=\"agentruntimes\"`\n121:   - Define class: `class AgentCubeProvider`\n122:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n123:   - Verification: `python -c \"from agentcube.services.agentcube_provider import AgentCubeProvider\"`\n124: \n125: - [ ] **T3.2**: Implement `AgentCubeProvider.__init__()`\n126:   - Parameters: `namespace: str = \"default\"`, `verbose: bool = False`, `kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None`\n127:   - Load kubeconfig\n128:   - Initialize APIs: `self.custom_api = kubernetes.client.CustomObjectsApi()`, `self.core_api = kubernetes.client.CoreV1Api()`\n129:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n130:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_agentcube_provider.py::TestAgentCubeProvider::test_init -v`\n131: \n132: - [ ] **T3.3**: Implement `_sanitize_name()` method (reuse pattern from KubernetesProvider)\n133:   - Same DNS-compliant sanitization logic\n134:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n135:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_agentcube_provider.py::TestAgentCubeProvider::test_sanitize_name -v`\n136: \n137: - [ ] **T3.4**: Implement `_ensure_namespace()` method\n138:   - Same pattern as KubernetesProvider\n139:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n140:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_agentcube_provider.py::TestAgentCubeProvider::test_ensure_namespace -v`\n141: \n142: - [ ] **T3.5**: Implement `deploy_agent_runtime()` method\n143:   - Parameters: `agent_name`, `image_url`, `port`, `entrypoint`, `env_vars`, `workload_manager_url`, `router_url`, `readiness_probe_path`, `readiness_probe_port`\n144:   - Validate required fields: `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`\n145:   - Build AgentRuntime CR body with spec\n146:   - Call `_ensure_namespace()`, `_sanitize_name()`\n147:   - Try `create_namespaced_custom_object()`, catch 409 → `patch_namespaced_custom_object()`\n148:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n149:   - Verification: `pytest cmd/cli/tests/test_agentcube_provider.py::TestAgentCubeProvider::test_deploy_agent_runtime -v`\n150: \n151: - [ ] **T3.6**: Implement AgentRuntime CR body template\n152:   - `apiVersion`: `\"{CR_GROUP}/{CR_VERSION}\"`\n153:   - `kind`: `\"AgentRuntime\"`\n154:   - `spec`: `image`, `port`, `entrypoint`, `sessionTimeout=\"15m\"`, `maxSessionDuration=\"8h